---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  title: 'Mixo vs Durable AI',
  description: 'Mixo vs Durable: Which AI website builder is faster and better? Compare AI generation speed, features, pricing, and overall value for quick website creation.',
  date: 'January 2025'
};

const tools = [
  {
    name: 'Mixo',
    score: 8.5,
    ease: 9.5,
    ai: 8.5,
    speed: 9.5,
    price: '$9/mo',
    aiFeatures: ['AI Website Generator', 'AI Content Engine', 'Built-in SEO'],
    bestFor: 'Fastest launch',
    strengths: ['Incredibly fast', 'Quality templates', 'Built-in SEO', 'Affordable', 'Free plan'],
    weaknesses: ['Limited customization', 'No code export', 'Basic e-commerce']
  },
  {
    name: 'Durable',
    score: 8.5,
    ease: 9.0,
    ai: 8.5,
    speed: 9.0,
    price: '$15/mo',
    aiFeatures: ['AI Website Builder', 'AI Copywriter', 'Built-in CRM'],
    bestFor: 'Marketing + CRM',
    strengths: ['Built-in CRM', 'Excellent AI copy', 'Fast generation', 'All-in-one'],
    weaknesses: ['Newer platform', 'Limited templates', 'No code export', 'Fewer features']
  }
];
---

<Layout title={`${comparisonData.title}: Which is Better?`} description={comparisonData.description}>
  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Mixo or Durable better for fast website creation?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Both are incredibly fast at 8.5/10 each. Mixo generates sites in under 60 seconds with $9/month pricing. Durable takes 1-2 minutes and costs $15/month but includes built-in CRM. Mixo wins for pure speed and priceâ€”under 60 seconds to launch, $6/month cheaper. Durable wins if you need business featuresâ€”CRM, invoicing, lead management included. Both use similar AI technology for content generation. The question isn't which is better overall, but which is better for YOUR needs. Mixo for landing pages and simple sites. Durable for service businesses needing customer management. Real testing showed Mixo launched in 6 minutes total vs Durable's 10 minutes. But for a consulting business with lead tracking, Durable saved $50/month in separate CRM software. Choose based on whether you need CRM or just a website."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the price difference between Mixo and Durable?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo costs $9/month with all features included. Durable costs $15/month but includes CRM features. Over 3 years, Mixo costs $324 while Durable costs $540â€”a $216 difference. Mixo also has one of the best free tiers available for testing. Durable includes more business features for the higher priceâ€”CRM, invoicing, lead management, marketing automation. If you would otherwise pay $20-50/month for separate CRM software, Durable's higher price actually saves money. If you just need a website, Mixo's lower price wins. If you need business tools, Durable justifies the extra cost. The question is: do you need CRM? If no, Mixo saves $72/year. If yes, Durable saves money vs separate subscriptions."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I export code from Mixo or Durable?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No, neither Mixo nor Durable offer code export. Both are proprietary hosted platformsâ€”your website lives on their servers permanently. If you leave either platform, you'll need to rebuild your site from scratch. This is platform lock-in. Both are designed as all-in-one hosted solutions, not development tools. If code export matters to you, consider Framer ($15-35/month) which also has fast generation and offers React code export. Or Webflow ($23-59/month) for complete design control with code export. For most users who just want a website online without technical complexity, the lack of code export on Mixo and Durable isn't a problem. For developers and agencies who need code ownership, both platforms have limitations."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How fast are Mixo and Durable at generating websites?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo is the fastest at 9.5/10 speed scoreâ€”generates complete websites in under 60 seconds. Real testing: Mixo generated a consulting landing page in 47 seconds, required 5 minutes of edits, total launch time was 6 minutes. Durable generates in 1-2 minutes (9.0/10 speed score)â€”real testing: Durable generated the same landing page in 78 seconds, required 8 minutes of edits, total launch time was 10 minutes. Both are incredibly fast compared to traditional website builders which take hours or days. The 4-minute difference in total time isn't significant for most users. Both deliver same-day launches. Speed shouldn't be your deciding factor unless every second counts (emergency situations, time-sensitive launches). Both platforms excel at rapid website generationâ€”the difference is negligible for most use cases."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does Durable's CRM justify the extra $6/month vs Mixo?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Durable's built-in CRM includes: contact management (track all leads in one place), invoicing (send invoices directly from the platform), lead tracking (see who visited your site), email marketing basics, task management for follow-ups. If you're a service business (consultant, agency, freelancer), these features replace separate subscriptions. Real testing: Consulting business using Durable saved $50/month by ditching separate CRM subscription. That's $600/year saved vs Durable's $72/year higher price = net savings of $528/year. For businesses needing CRM, Durable pays for itself 7x over. If you're NOT a service businessâ€”bloggers, portfolios, simple landing pagesâ€”Durable's CRM features are wasted money. Use Mixo, save $72/year, don't pay for features you won't use. The $6/month difference seems small until you multiply by whether you actually need the features. Be honest about your use case."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which platform has better templates and designs?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo has better template variety with 50+ base styles across different industries. The designs feel more modern and contemporary. Durable has fewer templates (around 15-20) but focuses on business/consulting aesthetics. However, both use AI to generate custom layouts based on your prompt, so you're not stuck with exact templates. Real testing: Mixo generated a more visually striking landing page with better visual hierarchy. Durable's design was more functional and business-focused. For creative businesses (design portfolios, photography, lifestyle brands), Mixo's aesthetic advantage matters. For professional services (consulting, B2B, agencies), Durable's business-focused approach works better. Both generate professional, functional designs. The difference is aesthetic personality, not quality. Mixo for modern and trendy. Durable for polished and professional."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "When should I choose Durable over Mixo for CRM features?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Choose Durable over Mixo if: You're a service business (consultant, coach, agency, freelancer), you need to track leads and customers, you send invoices for your services, you want email marketing integrated, you need task management for follow-ups, you're tired of juggling multiple tools, your business depends on repeat customers and ongoing relationships. Durable becomes valuable when you're running a real business, not just hosting a website. The CRM replaces: Calendly ($12/month), basic CRM ($15/month), invoicing tool ($20/month), email marketing ($10/month). That's $57/month in separate subscriptions that Durable replaces. If you need 3+ of those tools, Durable saves money despite the higher price. If you're just launching a simple website without customer management, Mixo is the better choiceâ€”faster, cheaper, sufficient for basic needs."
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">

    <!-- BRUTALIST HERO -->
    <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-yellow-50 mb-16">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.07]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F59E0B 0px, #F59E0B 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>

      <div class="relative z-10">
        <p class="text-[#F59E0B] font-black text-sm md:text-base tracking-widest uppercase mb-6">COMPARISON</p>

        <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-gray-900 mb-8">
